We have all kinds of tools at our disposal, and yes indeed I think our pets are the best in the game hands down (except that goofy 52 Fire pet, what's up with that? And what happened to his DS?!?!) but as a general rule people don't ever want us in their groups. We're certainly not a building block for a group. We're merely window dressing. And as far as benefits go, other classes have far more to offer their groups than we do. Afterall, there's no need for us to actually be in someone's group to make bandaids for them. And be truthful here, if your group said &quot;who's on root duty&quot; and you say &quot;my pet can root&quot; do you really expect anything but laughter in reply? Our pet procs are far too random and inconsistent to be counted upon. And as I head thru my 50s, I find them to be leaning heavier on the minor miracle side of the spectrum. And that of course is assuming you have a pet up and ready at your disposal, which for daily travel outside of a group is just not practicle.<br>
<br>
What I'm saying is, if Mages are not going to be viable group commodaties then by all means, give us the power to solo like there's no tomorrow. That means roots and snares and maybe even fears. OR give us some options that will open up new avenues for groups to do more when a Mage is with them. In any event, give us our own nitche. Even the Necro has more to offer a group or raid than a Mage does. And yet at the same time they can out-solo us at virtually every turn. It makes little sense to have them the more solo-friendly of the pet classes and also more welcome in groups. Let the Necros be the reigning solo champs. But let us then be the more group-friendly pet class, the one people would rather have at their side.<br>
<br>
So in recap, if nobody needs me as a Mage, make it so that I don't need them either. Or come up with options that make people in groups finally say &quot;Hey, get the Mage cuz he can...&quot; whatever that may be. Me? I'd rather see that occuring more often than just powering us up enough to deal with multiple mobs like the other solo classes. I want to be the Mage: the pet caster groups want and need. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udenadar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>denadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(3/18/02 12:44:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://julirama.homestead.com/files/denadar_60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Istaron</span><hr size=1> Earing of living slime 10wis/int 45hp/mana effect enstill  nec wiz mage enc. You want a root spell get a good group of 60s and head to cazic thule cause thats where this drops. <p>Den</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eskarina>Eskarina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/02 1:25:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Isarek</span><hr size=1> &quot;Our AAXP skills are geared for chain summoning (Quick Summoning, Elemantal Pact, Improved Reclaim Energy). As long as we are very effective at chain summoning pets, we will never get root.&quot;<br>
